'Donald Edwin "Don" Young' (born June 9, 1933) is the U.S. Representative for ,
serving since 1973. He is a member of the Republican Party.

Young is the dean of the Alaskan congressional delegation, the fifth most senior
U.S. Representative and the second most senior Republican Representative, behind
Bill Young of Florida.
